latestPosts.caption:
These items can cause trouble depending upon the comdition
.
1. Raw Sprouts (Alfalfa, Mung Bean, Radish)

Why to avoid:

May harbor harmful bacteria like E. coli or Salmonella, leading to foodborne illnesses.

2. Unpasteurized Milk and Dairy Products

Why to avoid:

➡ Can contain Listeria bacteria, increasing the risk of miscarriage or stillbirth.
.
3. Eggplant (Brinjal

TOMATO ) CHAR

Why to avoid:

Contains phytohormones that may stimulate menstruation, potentially leading to complications.

4. Fenugreek Leaves and Seeds (Methi)

Why to avoid:

→ High consumption may induce uterine contractions, increasing the risk of preterm Labor
.
5. Aloe Vera

Why to avoid:

➡ Contains anthraquinones, which can cause uterine contractions and potential miscarriage.

6. Bitter Gourd (Karela)

Why to avoid:

May lead to gastrointestinal issues and has compounds that can cause uterine contractions.
.
7. Ajinomoto (Monosodium Glutamate

MSG)

Why to avoid:

➡ Excessive intake may affect fetal brain development; commonly found in processed foods.

8. Certain Herbal Teas and Supplements

Why to avoid:

Some herbs can stimulate the uterus or have other adverse effects; always consult a Doctor 
.
have other adverse effects; always consult a healthcare provider before consumption.

9. High-Salt Foods (e.g., Pickles, Processed Snacks)

Why to avoid:

Excessive salt can lead to water retention and increased blood pressure.

10. Tulsi Leaves (Holy Basil)
10. Tulsi Leaves (Holy Basil)

Why to avoid:

➡ Contains compounds that may cause uterine contractions and has blood-thinning properties.
